This paper deals with the analysis of vehicular communication, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also incorporates the effect of different carrier frequencies, which involves signal processing and information theory (cs.IT). The use of Poisson cluster process (PCP) to model vehicle distribution involves mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The paper also deals with the design and analysis of urban V2X channels, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of three-dimensional (3D) ray-tracing simulation, which involves multimedia (cs.MM).
